snippet.textDisplay: Big, loud, obnoxious.... But it CAN COOL! Seriously, after gaming/rendering PC finishing for my friend with H150i Pro watercooler and seeing i9-9900K cooling results, got stumbled upon choice: do I want air or water CPU cooler in my upcoming PC. This thing though ticks nearly all cooling boxes, except it have loud fans. Though from other side it is not so expensive in comparing with large air CPU coolers. And after fan replacing to low noise 120mm fans like BeQuiet Silent Wings 2/3 it most likely will be nearly unhearable. Maybe IceGiant for modders in future would sell also only radiator part without fans?
snippet.textOriginal: Big, loud, obnoxious.... But it CAN COOL! snippet.textDisplay:
Absorption refrigerators are still used today in motor homes. The original absorption cooling systems used an ammonia based refrigerant. The refrigerant was heated by a gas pilot light or electric heating element which boiled the refrigerant causing it ti become a vapor and as it passed through the evaporator coil it absorbed heat and as it passed into and through the condenser coil it "lost" heat, dropping the temperature of the refrigerant to a point where it condensed back into a liquid. The absorption refrigeration method is the most basic type of a refrigeration system requiring the least mechanical fixtures to operate, no fans or motors.

This CPU Cooler makes a lot of sense to me and it applies the fundamental physics of the work I did for 30 years. Ima hafta get one!
